title: Hac’KP 2021
desc:
Today's cybercrimes are powered by supercomputers, artificial intelligence and complex algorithms. The vastness of this intangible medium makes it difficult for tracking down the wrong doers hidden in the dark web.
As part of the efforts to continually improve efficiency in handling various safety issues that we all face in this technological era, Kerala Police is organizing the 5th Edition of Hackathon “Hac’KP-2021”.

Hac’KP 2021 is an online platform for showcasing your talent and ideas to build solutions that can help uncover the DarkWeb. 
If you believe that you can contribute to this cause do participate in the World's Largest International Hackathon organized by the Kerala Police.
Whether you are a coder, designer, developer, analyst or an inventor, you can register at https://hackp.kerala.gov.in/.
The submissions are ending on 30 th April.
So don’t wait; Join Hac'KP, Discuss, Develop and Present your solutions.
Grab a chance to be a part of the force that is gearing up to crack down the DarkWeb.

I take this opportunity to thank Kerala Police Cyberdome for all their efforts to keep us safe.
I wish all the very Best for Hac’KP and its contestants. I request all my viewers to encourage this noble cause.
Let’s all be a part of the Kerala Police efforts in "Demistiyfying_the_DarkWeb"

Stay Safe and Thank you!
